===[[Kree Religions|Religions]]===
====[[Supreme Intelligence (Earth-616)|Supreme Intelligence]]====
As the Kree prized science and rational thought, they created a living God to those ideals: the [[Supreme Intelligence (Earth-616)|Supreme Intelligence]].{{r|X-Men Unlimited #5}} The worship of that creature was made the Kree official state religion.{{r|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Vol 2 7}}

The afterlife of the Kree is the [[Etherplex]].{{r|Chaos War: Dead Avengers #1}}

====Others====
An Kree Army officer and his crew once prayed to the "[[Gods of Pama]]". The prayer ended this way: ''"...and consign you to the gods of Pama, for your having died valiantly in battle... a death that the Kree appreciate above anything else. So say we all"''.{{r|Captain Marvel Vol 5 3}}

[[Korath-Thak (Earth-616)|Korath the Pursuer]] once made an omen to [[Gardar (Earth-616)|Gardar]],{{r|Annihilation: Ronan #3}} possibly a Kree god.

A [[Followers of Tam-Bor (Earth-616)|group of Kree]] also worshiped a being known as [[Tam-Bor]],{{r|Captain Marvel Vol 1 15|16}} and Mar-Vell had also invoked his name.{{r|Captain Marvel Vol 1 44}}

The ex-prime minister [[Zarek (Earth-616)|Zarek]] posed as a god-like being named Zo in order to seize control over the empire.{{r|Captain Marvel Vol 1 15|16}}

The government allowed the [[Universal Church of Truth (Earth-616)|Universal Church of Truth]] to erect temples throughout the Kree Empire, including on [[Kree-Lar (Planet)|Kree-Lar]].{{r|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Vol 2 7}}

Some Kree also gathered into secret sects of [[Cotati]] worshipers.{{r|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Vol 2 7}}

The creators of the Kree, the [[Progenitors]], have been called gods of the Kree,{{r|Royals #5}}{{r|Royals #6}} in the same way that the Kree have been called gods to the [[Inhomo supremis|Inhumans]].{{r|Royals #5}}

[[Sim-Del (Earth-616)|Sim-Del]], a Kree scientist, had researched and studied a God of Light who was able light an entire galaxy.{{r|Web of Venom: Wraith Vol 1 1}}

On [[Earth-1610]], the Kree worshiped the being known as Hala, who was also the alleged ancestor of [[Mahr Vehl (Earth-1610)|Mahr Vehl]].{{r|Ultimate Secret Vol 1 4}}

In the [[Cancerverse]], just like the majority of the beings, the Kree also worshiped the [[Many-Angled Ones]] following their takeover of the universe.{{r|Annihilation - Scourge: Silver Surfer Vol 1 1}}

====Atheism====
On [[Earth-200080]], the Kree were seemingly atheists, learning in their early childhood a mathematical equation proving the nonexistence of any deities.{{r|Dark Reign: The List - Wolverine #1}}

